==Details==
{{Quest details page|The Great Brain Robbery}}

==Walkthrough==
===Scouting===
{{Needed|4 planks, at least 20 nails, a hammer, [[fishbowl helmet]], and [[diving apparatus]].|recommended=A teleport to [[Edgeville Monastery]] if continuing to the next section immediately, and bring 3 [[watermelon seed]]s, a [[rake]], and a [[seed dibber]] to complete the hard [[Morytania Diary]] task.}}
:'''Note:''' Don't bring any [[pet]]s!
{{Map|name=Brother Tranquility|x=3681|y=2963|r=3|mtype=square|align=right|width=250|height=250|caption=The quest's start point.}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Brother Tranquility]] on [[Mos Le'Harmless]] near the dock. {{Chat option|1}} (Finish the dialogue, or you will be teleported back to Mos Le' Harmless)
**When doing the Hard [[Morytania Diary]] task, plant [[watermelon seed]]s now to be able to harvest them at the end of the quest.
**Beware of aggressive Level 57 [[Zombie pirate]]s throughout the island.
*Leave the windmill and head north, pull on the statue and climb down.
*Equip your diving apparatus and fishbowl then descend.
*Repair the stairs at the end of the tunnel and climb up.
*Climb up the ladder then peer through the peephole.
*Return to [[Brother Tranquility]], talk to him to be transported back to Mos Le' Harmless {{Chat option|1}}, then talk to him again there.}}

===The prayer book===
{{Needed|A [[Holy symbol]]|recommended=[[Ectophial]]}}
{{Checklist|*Go to the [[Edgeville Monastery]] and search the bookcase in the south-west corner of the {{FloorNumber|uk=0}}. (This is a good time to bless your symbol if it isn't already, see [[Brother Jered]])
*Read the book.
*Equip a [[Holy Symbol]] and return to [[Mos Le' Harmless]].
*Talk to [[Brother Tranquility]] to return to Harmony Island.
*Right click the book "recite prayer" inside of the windmill.
*Talk to Brother Tranquility. {{Chat option|1}}
}}

===The doctor===
{{Needed|[[Ring of Charos]], 4 [[plank]]s (14 if making the [[wooden cat]]s, 10 pieces of fur), 10 wooden cats, 100 nails (to be sure you have enough), and a hammer, 2 free spaces. Crate parts and wolf whistle are needed but obtained during this section.|recommended=Ectophial or Mos' Le Harmless teleport scroll to teleport away once the final step is complete.}}
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Dr Fenkenstrain]] (jail on the top floor of his castle north-east of [[Canifis]]).
** To get to the jail take the stairs to the east or west.
** Walk through the metal gate.
** Go up the ladder.
*Equip your [[Ring of Charos]], keep it equipped through this section.
*Talk to [[Rufus]] in Canifis (food store). {{Chat option|1}} (until you receive a [[wolf whistle]] and a [[crate part]])
*Make 10 [[wooden cat]]s on a clockmaker's bench in your house (10 planks and 10 furs).
*Build a crate next to Dr Fenkenstrain, add a false bottom (4 planks and nails), and fill it with the wooden cats.
*Blow the wolf whistle.
*Rufus will appear and will give you a [[Shipping order]].
*Put the Shipping order on the crate.
}}

===Making the transplants===
{{Needed|A hammer (the [[Imcando hammer]] does not work), fishbowl helmet, diving apparatus, combat equipment and 6 empty inventory slots.}}
{{Checklist|
*Return to [[Harmony]] island and enter the windmill basement.
*Talk to [[Dr Fenkenstrain]].
*Equip your diving equipment before leaving the windmill and go north to the shipwreck.
*Search the locker for a fuse. Climb the ladder and get a tinderbox and a keg.
*Go south a bit to the monastery and use the keg and fuse on the door. Light the fuse.
*Enter and kill 4 [[Sorebones]] for a Cranial clamp, Brain tongs, 3 Bell jars, and 30 Skull staples.
*Climb-down the ladder in the mill and talk to Dr Fenkenstrain.
*Climb up and talk to [[Brother Tranquility]], prepare for the fight.
}}

===The big battle===
{{Needed|Combat equipment, fishbowl helmet and diving apparatus.}}
{{Instance}}
{{Checklist|
*Return to the Harmony island monastery and Confront [[Mi-Gor]] to start the fight against [[Barrelchest]].
**You must wear your fishbowl helmet and diving apparatus.
**Each attack will disable your prayer and remove a few prayer points.
**When adjacent he will only attack with melee.
**Re-enabling prayer after each attack will prevent you from taking any damage.
**Alternatively you can leave the monastery and re-enter; the boss will get stuck and can be safespotted from the entrance.
*Talk to [[Brother Tranquility]].
}}
'''Quest complete!'''

